6quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppearing%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20Mayim%20Bialik's%20%26quot%3BBreakdown%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20which%20was%20released%20on%20December%2016%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-ceo-mustafa-suleyman-cost-hundred-billions-superintelligence-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMustafa%20Suleyman%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20companionship%20and%20support%20have%20become%20some%20of%20AI's%20most%20popular%20use%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20using%20AI%20chatbots%20for%20everything%20from%20navigating%20breakups%20to%20solving%20disagreements%20with%20family%20members%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20therapy%2C%26quot%3B%20Suleyman%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20because%20these%20models%20were%20designed%20to%20be%20nonjudgmental%2C%20nondirectional%2C%20and%20with%20nonviolent%20communication%20as%20their%20primary%20method%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20even-handed%2C%20have%20reflective%20listening%2C%20to%20be%20empathetic%2C%20to%20be%20respectful%2C%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20something%20that%20the%20world%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upside%20of%20this%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20a%20way%20to%20spread%20kindness%20and%20love%20and%20to%20detoxify%20ourselves%20so%20that%20we%20can%20show%20up%20in%20the%20best%20way%20that%20we%20possible%20can%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%20with%20the%20humans%20that%20we%20love.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuleyman%20cofounded%20DeepMind%20in%202010.%20The%20company%20was%20acquired%20by%20Google%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20podcast%2C%20he%20said%20people%20need%20a%20space%20to%20%26quot%3Bask%20a%20stupid%20question%2C%20repeatedly%2C%20in%20a%20private%20way%2C%20without%20feeling%20embarrassed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20he%20said%2C%20chatbots%20can%20make%20people%20%26quot%3Bfeel%20seen%20and%20understood%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20way%20that%20many%20other%20humans%20can't%2C%20outside%20of%20partners%20or%20close%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20in%20tech%2C%20however%2C%20is%20enthusiastic%20about%20chatbots%20being%20used%20as%20therapy%20stand-ins.%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20is%20one%20of%20those%20voices.%20In%20August%202025%2C%20he%20expressed%20his%20discomfort%20over%20people%20relying%20on%20chatbots%20to%20make%20major%20life%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20imagine%20a%20future%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20really%20trust%20ChatGPT's%20advice%20for%20their%20most%20important%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BAlthough%20that%20could%20be%20great%2C%20it%20makes%20me%20uneasy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202025%2C%20while%20appearing%20on%20%26quot%3BThis%20Past%20Weekend%20with%20Theo%20Von%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20also%20flagged%20the%20potential%20legal%20risks%20of%20offloading%20onto%20a%20robot.%20He%20said%20that%20OpenAI%20may%20be%20required%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-privacy-therapy-sam-altman-openai-lawsuit-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eproduce%20its%20users'%20therapy-style%20chats%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMental%20health%20professionals%20have%20voiced%20concerns%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-therapy-risks-benefits-boundaries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20ChatGPT%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%20Speaking%20to%20Business%20Insider%20senior%20health%20reporter%20Julia%20Pugachevsky%20in%20March%202025%2C%20two%20therapists%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-psychosis-induced-explained-examples-by-psychiatrist-patients-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erelying%20on%20AI%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20emotional%20support%20could%20exacerbate%20loneliness%20and%20make%20people%20dependent%20on%20seeking%20r