%20very%20rarely%20go%20out%20to%20eat.%20I%20went%20out%20to%20some%20food%20trucks%20with%20my%20four-person%20family%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20of%20them%20is%20only%20one%20year%20old%2C%20so%20she%20doesn't%20eat%20that%20much%20%E2%80%94%20but%20we%20had%20a%20couple%20beers%2C%20a%20hamburger%2C%20some%20meat%20on%20a%20stick%2C%20and%20it%20was%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%20you%20could%20go%20as%20a%20family%20to%20a%20Michelin%20restaurant%20for%20%24100.%20The%20scale%20is%20totally%20different%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-japan-and-am-saving-more-than-1800-a-month-on-rent-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20quality%20is%20totally%20different%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20what%20people%20don't%20realize%20is%20that%20not%20just%20Japanese%20food%20is%20good%20in%20Japan%2C%20all%20food%20in%20Japan%20is%20good%20%E2%80%94%20except%20Mexican.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20got%20French%2C%20Italian%2C%20great%20hamburgers%2C%20pizza%2C%20fried%20chicken%20%E2%80%94%20so%20many%20different%20international%20cuisines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverything%20that%20you%20stop%20by%2C%20even%20a%20little%20hole-in-the-wall%20is%20going%20to%20be%20really%20good.%20Whereas%20I%20felt%2C%20especially%20at%20those%20food%20trucks%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it's%20like%20mediocre%20Asian%20food%2C%20hamburgers%2C%20pizza%2C%20and%20tacos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20available%20in%20suburbs%20in%20the%20States%20is%20limited%20and%20expensive%2C%20whereas%20in%20a%20small%20city%20in%20Japan%2C%20you've%20got%20lots%20of%20international%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f61462c-c7c2-4c96-a886-da6f01dcc0eb%5C%22%3EA%20high%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20a%20poor%20job%20market%20in%20the%20US%20drove%20me%20back%20to%20Japan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20what%20we%20could%20to%20control%20our%20costs.%20We%20left%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20went%20to%20a%20small%20town%20in%20southern%20Washington%2C%20but%20costs%20just%20kept%20creeping%20up.%20And%20then%20there%20were%20changes%20with%20our%20jobs%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20company%20seemed%20like%20every%20six%20months%20it%20was%20going%20through%20some%20kind%20of%20layoffs%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20my%20turn%20was%20going%20to%20come%20at%20some%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20when%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20use%20my%20other%20skills%20in%20life%20to%20develop%20a%20business.%20And%2C%20this%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20meta%2C%20but%20I%20made%20a%20business%20to%20teach%20people%20how%20to%20move%20to%20Japan%20on%20their%20own%20terms%2C%20because%20that's%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20was%20doing%20that%2C%20getting%20the%20website%20all%20set%20up%20and%20getting%20my%20first%20clients%2C%20I%20got%20the%20notice%20that%20it%20was%20my%20turn%2C%20and%20my%20job%20was%20going%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20having%20a%20conversation%20in%20a%20coffee%20shop.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6942ed2764858d02d216fa2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWoolsey%20started%20a%20business%20helping%20others%20move%20and%20work%20in%20Japan.%3Cp%3EJapan%20Remotely%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20that%20summer%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20her%20company%20came%20to%20an%20agreement%20that%20their%20time%20together%20was%20also%20finished.%20We%20went%20from%20two%20incomes%20and%20a%20startup%20to%20just%20a%20startup.%20And%20that%20was%20the%20point%20where%20the%20golden%20handcuffs%20were%20off.%20We%20could%20do%20anything.%20We%20could%20go%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20three%20choices%3A%20We%20could%20try%20to%20work%20remotely%20or%20get%20something%20locally%20in%20this%20small%20town%20where%20it's%20harder%20than%20ever%20to%20find%20remote%20work%3B%20we%20could%20get%20a%20job%20in%20DC%2C%20New%2