%5C%22%3EStarbucks%20Card%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20more%20than%20a%20gift%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20an%20invitation%20to%20pause%2C%20connect%2C%20and%20share%20a%20moment%20with%20someone%20you%20care%20about%20or%20treat%20yourself%20to%20something%20you%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20Tressie%20Lieberman%2C%20Starbucks'%20global%20chief%20brand%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20proud%20to%20be%20a%20beloved%20brand%20and%20honored%20that%20Starbucks%20Cards%20remain%20a%20go-to%20gift%20during%20the%20holiday%20season.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGift%20cards%20are%20big%20business%20in%20the%20retail%20sector.%20A%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20found%20that%20gift%20cards%20are%20the%20second%20most%20popular%20gift%20this%20season%2C%20with%2043%25%20of%20shoppers%20planning%20to%20purchase%20at%20least%20one%20gift%20card.%20Total%20spending%20on%20gift%20cards%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%20%2429%20billion%20this%20year.%20For%20brands%20like%20Starbucks%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Target%2C%20and%20other%20top%20sellers%2C%20that%20means%20a%20big%20payday%20wrapped%20in%20a%20small%20package.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Starbucks'%20most%20recent%20financial%20filings%2C%20the%20company%20held%20%241.8%20billion%20in%20unredeemed%20gift%20card%20funds%20as%20of%20September%2028%2C%20up%20from%20%241.7%20billion%20at%20the%20same%20time%20last%20year.%20In%20comparison%2C%20Target%20held%20%241.2%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebillion%20as%20of%20February%2C%20while%C2%A0Amazon%C2%A0held%20%245.4%20billion%20as%20of%20December%2031%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225287aa24-abb4-4e49-8278-a3355a889b89%5C%22%3EA%20gift%20that%20keeps%20on%20giving%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGift%20cards%20are%20especially%20valuable%20to%20companies%20because%20they%20collect%20lump%20sums%20of%20cash%20upfront%2C%20often%20months%20before%20delivering%20a%20product%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20without%20having%20to%20deliver%20one%20at%20all.%20Based%20on%20historical%20spending%20patterns%2C%20companies%20can%20project%20that%20a%20portion%20of%20gift%20card%20balances%20will%20never%20be%20redeemed%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20recognize%20that%20unused%20money%20as%20revenue%2C%20a%20process%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bbreakage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20fiscal%20year%2C%20Starbucks%20recognized%20roughly%20%24200%20million%20in%20breakage%20revenue%20from%20company-operated%20stores%20and%20%2422%20million%20from%20its%20licensed%20locations%2C%20according%20to%20its%20annual%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Target%20nor%20Amazon%20makes%20their%20breakage%20rates%20explicit%20in%20their%20filings%3B%20instead%2C%20they%20roll%20estimated%20breakage%20into%20reported%20gift%20card%20issuance%20figures%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20directly%20compare%20with%20companies%20like%20Starbucks%2C%20which%20separately%20disclose%20breakage%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20more%20often%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-hit-with-boycott-programs-such-as-gift-card-trade-in-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egift%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20spent%20by%20their%20recipients%2C%20helping%20drive%20repeat%20visits%20and%20introducing%20or%20strengthening%20customers'%20relationships%20with%20a%20retailer's%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20customers%20register%20a%20gift%20card%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-to-cut-25-star-bonus-revamp-rewards-reusable-cups-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarbucks%20Rewards%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20can%20earn%20points%20toward%20free%20drinks%20and%20food%2C%20encouraging%20repeat%20visits%20that%20often%20result%20in%20spending%20exceeding%20the%20card's%20original%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20introduced%20its%20first%20gift%20card%20in%202001%2C%20when%20it%20had%20fewer%20than%205%2C000%20stores%20worldwide.%20It%20was%2