26quot%3B%20Trump%20added%20in%20the%20national%20speech%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%2C%20in%20a%20December%20press%20release%2C%20also%20touted%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20trade%20deficit%20has%20narrowed%20to%20its%20smallest%20since%20mid-2020%26quot%3B%20in%20September%2C%20citing%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bmore%20proof%20that%20President%20Donald%20J.%20Trump's%20America%20First%20trade%20agenda%20is%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKimberly%20Clausing%2C%20professor%20of%20tax%20law%20and%20policy%20at%20the%20UCLA%20School%20of%20Law%20and%20a%20previous%20official%20at%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20the%20Treasury%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20despite%20the%20negative%20association%20with%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bdeficit%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20smaller%20trade%20deficit%20could%20simply%20mean%20that%20people%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-biggest-economic-mistake-prices-affordability-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epulling%20back%20on%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20investing%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20United%20States%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20a%20declining%20trade%20deficit%20is%20often%20associated%20with%20a%20weak%20economy%2C%20due%20to%20reduced%20consumption%20and%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Clausing.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BThat%20may%20be%20the%20case%20now%20as%20well%2C%20since%20some%20market%20indicators%20show%20economic%20weakness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%2C%20the%20total%20volume%20of%20both%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eexports%20and%20imports%2C%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%20was%20in%20decline%20for%20three%20months%20preceding%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f41a462b-3a1a-46bb-8f23-994de5ae97ba%5C%22%3EThe%20effect%20of%20tariffs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20steady%20stock%20market%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20showing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-purchases-financial-risks-economic-uncertainty-real-estate-careers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esigns%20of%20weakness%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20inflation%20slowed%20in%20November%2C%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20warned%20that%20the%20data%20may%20have%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20government%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariff%20measures%20are%20already%20exerting%20measurable%20upward%20pressure%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econsumer%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20report%20published%20in%20October%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20of%20St.%20Louis%20that%20looked%20at%20data%20from%20January%20to%20August%20of%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rise%20in%20prices%20beginning%20in%20early%202025%20coincides%20closely%20with%20tariff%20developments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20reported%20that%20the%20country%20lost%20105%2C000%20jobs%20in%20October%20and%20added%2064%2C000%20jobs%20in%20November%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-from-november-jobs-report-unemployment-job-growth-earnings-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20rose%20to%20a%20four-year%20high%20of%204.6%25%20in%20the%20past%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-immigration-prices-manufacturing-tariffs-america-economy-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edomestic%20manufacturing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20reported%2012%2C706%2C000%20employees%20in%20the%20sector%20as%20of%20September%202025%2C%20down%2049%2C000%20from%20a%20base%20of%2012%2C755%2C000%20employees%20at%20the%20end%20of%20January%202025%2C%20when%20Trump%20took%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinegarden%20said%20that%20tariffs%20create%20an%20opportunity%20cost%2C%20because%20when%20more%20money%20is%20spent%20either%20by%20paying%20taxes%20on%20a%20foreign%20good%20or%20on%20a%20domestic%20product%20that%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20that%20reduces%20the%20nation's%20power%20to%20buy%2C%20invest%2C%20and%20hire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20buying%20the%20least%20cost-efficient%20option%2C%20you're%20subsidizing%20jobs%20that%20are%20less%20efficient%2C%20and%20sentiments%20aside%2C%20that's%20bad%20for%20long-term%20job%20creation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Winegarden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Furman%2C%20professor%20of%20the%20practice%20of%20economic%20policy%20at%20the%20Harvard%20Kennedy%20School%2C%20also%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20perception%20that%20tariffs%20have%20decreased%20trade%20deficits%20may%20be%20false%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20and%20they%20did%20not%20create%20any%20fiscal%20benefits%20for%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20trade%20deficit%20%E2%80%94%20it%20has%20not%20actually%20narrowed.%20There%20has%20just%20been%20a%20timing%20shift%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Furman.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20happened%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20imports%20were%20pulled%20forward%20and%20ended%20up%20being%20unusually%20large%20in%20Dec%202024%20through%20March%202025%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau's%20International%20Trade%20in%20Goods%20and%20Services%20report%2C%20the%20national%20trade%20deficit%20was%20%2495.2%20billion%20larger%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%202025%20than%20in%20the%20same%20period%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20are%20bringing%20in%20substantial%20revenue%2C%20but%20that%20revenue%20is%20largely%20offsetting%20other%20tax%20cuts%20done%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Furman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%26quot%3B%20Furman%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20meaningful%20portion%20of%20the%20tariff%20revenue%20is%20coming%20from%20American%20consumers%20in%20the%20form%20of%20higher%20prices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-paint-a-complicated-picture-of-trumps-economic-outcomes-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766406841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69445d3564858d02d21716eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-paint-a-complicated-picture-of-trumps-economic-outcomes-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20is%20touting%20tariff%20revenues%20and%20a%20shrinking%20trade%20deficit%20as%20his%20economic%20accomplishments%20ahead%20or%20midterms%2C%20but%20economists%20say%20it's%20complicated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A64%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-paint-a-complicated-picture-of-trumps-economic-outcomes-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CBSE%20announces%20orientation%20programme%20on%20entrance%20exams%20for%20faculties%20in%20UP%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766406718000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-126121993%2Cimgsize-555006.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Feducation%2Fnews%2Fcbse-announces-orientation-programme-on-entrance-exams-and-career-pathways-for-principals-counsellors-in-up-check-direct-link-to-register-here%2Farticleshow%2F126121802.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CBSE%20has%20rescheduled%20its%20Orientation%20Programme%20on%20Entrance%20Exams%20and%20Career%20Pathways%20for%20Principals%20and%20Counsellors%20in%20Shahjahanpur%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20Originally%20postpon