0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnikes-wins-and-losses-with-win-now-strategy-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwin%20now%26quot%3B%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Hill%20described%20it%20on%20last%20week's%20earnings%20call%20as%20Nike's%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20response%20to%20our%20biggest%20challenges%20and%20opportunities%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0focuses%20on%20five%20key%20areas%3A%20culture%2C%20product%2C%20marketing%2C%20marketplace%2C%20and%20in-person%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20leans%20on%20a%20sports-driven%20reset%20that%20has%20%26quot%3Brealigned%26quot%3B%20about%208%2C000%20employees%20around%20its%20core%20sports%20categories%2C%20the%20company%20said.%20Those%20categories%20include%20running%2C%20basketball%2C%20football%2C%20and%20training%2C%20as%20well%20as%20sportswear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20to%20put%20the%20athlete%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20center%20of%20everything%20that%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Hill%20said%20in%20a%20March%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20running%20category%20is%20leading%20the%20effort%20and%20reflects%20the%20direction%20Hill%20is%20steering%20the%20company.%20Nike%20said%20its%20running%20business%20grew%20by%20more%20than%2020%25%20last%20quarter%2C%20which%20ended%20in%20November%2C%20marking%20the%20second%20consecutive%20period%20of%20comparable%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f091abe2-ffa1-41f7-a471-7132237b972b%5C%22%3ENike's%20senior%20leadership%20team%20got%20a%20revamp%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHill%20shook%20up%20Nike's%20leadership%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20he%20restructured%20its%20consumer%2C%20product%2C%20and%20brand%20leadership%20to%20focus%20on%20three%20areas%3A%20consumer%20and%20sport%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20product%20creation.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20overhaul%2C%20Nike's%20former%20president%20of%20consumer%2C%20product%2C%20and%20brand%20retired%2C%20and%20Hill%20promoted%20four%20other%20Nike%20insi