.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Faloe-vera-3-1723014113-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Faloe-vera-3-1723014113-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Faloe-vera-3-1723014113-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Faloe-vera-3-1723014113-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-360104%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EHrushikesh%20says%20farmers%20can%20earn%20good%20profits%20if%20they%20make%20products%20from%20aloe%20vera%20like%20juice%2C%20soaps%2C%20and%20fertilisers.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20bid%20to%20run%20a%20business%20from%20the%20village%2C%20he%20started%20a%20nursery%20by%20selling%20moringa%20and%20mango%20saplings.%20However%2C%20this%20business%20would%20peak%20only%20during%20the%20monsoon.%20Gradually%2C%20he%20started%20selling%20fertilisers%20to%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20turning%20point%20came%20into%20his%20life%20in%202007%20when%20farmers%20were%20throwing%20aloe%20vera%20plants%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETurned%20adversity%20into%20opportunity%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHrushikesh%20planted%204%2C000%20discarded%20aloe%20vera%20plants%20between%20mango%20and%20%3Cem%3Eamla%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20gooseberry)%20trees.%20%E2%80%9CI%20thought%20there%20was%20no%20harm%20in%20growing%20aloe%20vera%20on%20my%20farm%2C%20even%20if%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20generate%20immediate%20income.%20I%20knew%20that%20aloe%20vera%20could%20work%20wonders%20as%20a%20termite%20repellent%20and%20would%20help%20protect%20my%20mango%20trees%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20graduate%2C%20who%20holds%20a%20bachelor%E2%80%99s%20degree%20in%20horticulture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20offline%20exhibitions%20organised%20in%20Satara%2C%20he%20often%20came%20a