%9D%20says%20Sanchita%20Daswani%2C%20a%20Hong%20Kong-based%20nutritionist.%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20rich%20in%20vitamins%2C%20antioxidants%2C%20and%20even%20protein%20in%20small%20quantities.%20And%20when%20children%20participate%20in%20planting%20and%20plucking%20them%2C%20they%20develop%20a%20real%20connection%20with%20food.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%20that%20parents%20often%20underestimate%20how%20versatile%20these%20tiny%20greens%20are.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20sprinkle%20them%20on%20parathas%2C%20stuff%20them%20into%20wraps%2C%20or%20even%20blend%20them%20into%20chutneys.%20Once%20kids%20start%20growing%20them%2C%20they%20actually%20get%20excited%20to%20eat%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandhya%20Narasimhan%2C%20a%20Thane-based%20clinical%20nutritionist%20and%20lactation%20counsellor%2C%20agrees%20on%20their%20potency%3A%20%E2%80%9CMicrogreens%20are%20power-packed%20with%20iron%2C%20selenium%2C%20magnesium%20%E2%80%94%20nutrients%20that%20play%20a%20huge%20role%20in%20children%E2%80%99s%20growth%2C%20mood%2C%20and%20cognitive%20development.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-09-05T142603.207-1757062577.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sandhya%20Narasimhan%20is%20a%20Thane-based%20clinical%20nutritionist%20and%20lactation%20counsellor.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-09-05T142603.207-1757062577.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-09-05T142603.207-1757062577-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-09-05T142603.207-1757062577-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-medi